# Order Rules

- Enforce explicit state machine transitions (draft -> pending -> paid/fulfilled/cancelled/refunded).
- Forbid invalid jumps (e.g., cancelled -> fulfilled).
- Persist immutable commercial facts at order placement (prices, taxes, discounts, item details).
- Ensure retries do not duplicate orders, captures, or shipments (idempotency keys where needed).
- Keep order numbers unique and tenant-scoped (or globally unique by design).
